This paper deals with the performance analysis of LDPC codes under belief-propagation decoding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of potential functions, which are commonly used in statistical physics, to simplify the proof technique. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and possibly to the sub-categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper deals with large-system limits and ensembles, which are concepts that are often studied in the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
